    "domain_description": "The UKMLA Applied Knowledge Test assesses the knowledge required for safe practice as a UK Foundation doctor. It emphasizes clinical decision-making, patient safety, evidence-based practice, and professional values. The exam covers breadth across all medical specialties with focus on common presentations, emergency management, and primary care contexts. Questions test application of knowledge rather than recall, integrating basic sciences with clinical practice. Strong emphasis on communication, ethics, prescribing safety, and public health responsibilities.",
